⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of St. Petersburg
node CRP · CRP · ⟦St. Petersburg:CRP:732c70⟧

WHO   — St. Petersburg — the city as fever
WHAT  — The novel's living setting: heat, canals, garrets, taverns, and crowds, an oppressive stage that breeds Raskolnikov's fever.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Dostoevsky's Petersburg is not backdrop but pressure — the modern city as a hot, crowded, isolating machine for despair.
HOW   — By summer heat, poverty, dust, and the dense indifferent crowd in which a man can be utterly alone.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the hot, crowded, golden-rotten city that presses a poor man into his garret and his fever until a theory looks like a way out.

